description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Programme and Operations Team (POT) is a central team responsible for providing a number of services across the System Transformation Team. The team is responsible for governance and assurance across the team, providing a PMO and business service to all teams. Additionally, the team leads OD, HR and Finance functions, providing dedicated support as needed to all programmes.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The post sits within the Finance function within POT. This function provides the Directors of the System Transformation team and other SMT members with assurance and oversight of all budgetary activity associated with delivery of their key accountabilities..&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;As a business support officer supporting the finance function, the post holder will hold:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Significant previous experience in a business support role with a wide range of experience and skills in particular finance, or equivalent experience of working in a large, complex organisation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Excellent administrative skills, including the ability to construct clear, grammatically correct emails, letters and reports at a high standard of presentation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Highly developed organisational skills with exception attention to detail.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to adapt to change to change and to develop services and systems to meet changing needs.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Excellent time management skills with the ability to re-prioritise. Skills for communication on complex information and administrative matters, requiring developed interpersonal and oral/ written communication skills.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to pull together comprehensive draft reports, data and letters. Negotiating, networking and persuasive skills.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Ability to work without supervision and work on own initiative, organising and prioritising own and others workloads to changing and often tight deadlines.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Adam Westerman&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: adam.westerman@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 07730 376172&lt;/p&gt;
